@startuml
left to right direction
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho
hide empty members

class Server {
  +mount auth routes
  +mount reservation routes
  +mount restaurant routes
  +mount review routes
}

class AuthRoute {
  +POST /api/v1/auth/register
  +POST /api/v1/auth/login
  +GET /api/v1/auth/me
  +GET /api/v1/auth/logout
}

class ReservationRoute {
  +GET /api/v1/reservations
  +GET /api/v1/reservations/{id}
  +POST /api/v1/restaurants/{restaurantId}/reservations
  +PUT /api/v1/reservations/{id}
  +DELETE /api/v1/reservations/{id}
}

class RestaurantRoute {
  +GET /api/v1/restaurants
  +GET /api/v1/restaurants/{id}
  +POST /api/v1/restaurants
  +PUT /api/v1/restaurants/{id}
  +DELETE /api/v1/restaurants/{id}
}

class ReviewRoute {
  +GET /api/v1/reviews
  +GET /api/v1/reviews/{id}
  +POST /api/v1/restaurants/{restaurantId}/reviews
  +PUT /api/v1/reviews/{id}
  +DELETE /api/v1/reviews/{id}
}

class AuthController {
  +register()
  +login()
  +getMe()
  +logout()
}

class ReservationController {
  +getReservations()
  +getReservation()
  +addReservation()
  +updateReservation()
  +deleteReservation()
}

class RestaurantController {
  +getRestaurants()
  +getRestaurant()
  +createRestaurant()
  +updateRestaurant()
  +deleteRestaurant()
}

class ReviewController {
  +getReviews()
  +getReview()
  +addReview()
  +updateReview()
  +deleteReview()
}

class User {
  +_id
  +name
  +email
  +role
}

class Restaurant {
  +_id
  +name
  +address
  +tel
}

class Reservation {
  +_id
  +resDate
  +user
  +restaurant
}

class Review {
  +_id
  +title
  +rating
  +user
  +restaurant
}

class AuthMiddleware {
  +protect()
  +authorize(...roles)
}

class Database {
  +connectDB()
}
note bottom of Database
Model relationship summary:
- User makes many Reservations
- Restaurant has many Reservations
- User writes many Reviews
- Restaurant has many Reviews
- Each Reservation belongs to exactly one User and one Restaurant
- Each Review belongs to exactly one User and one Restaurant
end note

Server --> AuthRoute : uses
Server --> ReservationRoute : uses
Server --> RestaurantRoute : uses
Server --> ReviewRoute : uses

AuthRoute --> AuthController : maps requests to
ReservationRoute --> ReservationController : maps requests to
RestaurantRoute --> RestaurantController : maps requests to
ReviewRoute --> ReviewController : maps requests to

AuthRoute --> AuthMiddleware : protect / me
ReservationRoute --> AuthMiddleware : protect routes
ReviewRoute --> AuthMiddleware : protect write routes
RestaurantRoute --> AuthMiddleware : protect admin routes

AuthController --> User
ReservationController --> Reservation
ReservationController --> User
ReservationController --> Restaurant
RestaurantController --> Restaurant
ReviewController --> Review
ReviewController --> User
ReviewController --> Restaurant

Database --> User
Database --> Reservation
Database --> Restaurant
Database --> Review

User "1" --> "0..*" Reservation : makes
Restaurant "1" --> "0..*" Reservation : receives
User "1" --> "0..*" Review : writes
Restaurant "1" --> "0..*" Review : has
Reservation "0..*" --> "1" User : belongs to
Reservation "0..*" --> "1" Restaurant : for
Review "0..*" --> "1" User : authored by
Review "0..*" --> "1" Restaurant : about

note right of AuthController
Routes handled:
- POST /api/v1/auth/register -> register()
- POST /api/v1/auth/login -> login()
- GET /api/v1/auth/me -> getMe()
- GET /api/v1/auth/logout -> logout()
end note

note right of ReservationController
Routes handled:
- GET /api/v1/reservations -> getReservations()
- GET /api/v1/reservations/{id} -> getReservation()
- POST /api/v1/restaurants/{restaurantId}/reservations -> addReservation()
- PUT /api/v1/reservations/{id} -> updateReservation()
- DELETE /api/v1/reservations/{id} -> deleteReservation()
end note

note right of RestaurantController
Routes handled:
- GET /api/v1/restaurants -> getRestaurants()
- GET /api/v1/restaurants/{id} -> getRestaurant()
- POST /api/v1/restaurants -> createRestaurant()
- PUT /api/v1/restaurants/{id} -> updateRestaurant()
- DELETE /api/v1/restaurants/{id} -> deleteRestaurant()
end note

note right of ReviewController
Routes handled:
- GET /api/v1/reviews -> getReviews()
- GET /api/v1/reviews/{id} -> getReview()
- POST /api/v1/restaurants/{restaurantId}/reviews -> addReview()
- PUT /api/v1/reviews/{id} -> updateReview()
- DELETE /api/v1/reviews/{id} -> deleteReview()
end note
@enduml